The article is a statement made by the President regarding food safety. The President acknowledges the efforts made by the Food Safety Working Group in upgrading the food safety system. Steps have been taken to reduce the prevalence of E. coli, exposure to Campylobacter, and Salmonella contamination. The FDA has conducted a pilot study on a tracing system, and a new website has been launched to provide consumers with information on food recalls. The President thanks the House for their support and urges the Senate to pass the FDA Food Safety Modernization Act, which aims to address challenges in the food safety system and promote a prevention-oriented approach.